# Universal UI (Theme + DX Defaults)

Keep the UI dense, dark-first, and low-chroma. Prefer semantic HTML + Pico defaults; only add CSS for layout and deliberate components.

## Pico Sand (baseline)

Include Pico Sand:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@picocss/pico@2/css/pico.sand.min.css">
```

Enable dark theme via `data-theme="dark"` on the root `<html>` (see `app/templates/index.html`).

## Project Theme Overrides (source of truth)

All theme token overrides live in `app/static/css/app.css` under `[data-theme="dark"]`.

```css
[data-theme="dark"] {
  /* Zinc backgrounds */
  --pico-background-color: #09090b;
  --pico-card-background-color: #18181b;
  --pico-muted-border-color: rgba(63, 63, 70, 0.4);
  --pico-form-element-background-color: #18181b;
  --pico-form-element-border-color: rgba(63, 63, 70, 0.4);
  --pico-form-element-active-background-color: #18181b;

  /* Warm text tones */
  --pico-base-color: #c8c2b4;
  --pico-h6-color: #f0ece4;
  --pico-h5-color: #e0dbd0;
  --pico-h4-color: #c8c2b4;
  --pico-h3-color: #b8b2a4;
  --pico-h2-color: #a8a294;
  --pico-h1-color: #908878;
  --pico-muted-color: #8a8070;
  --pico-form-element-placeholder-color: var(--pico-h3-color);
  --pico-form-element-color: #e4dfd6;
}
```

